01:45:38,991 --> 01:45:41,832
I had a question that is maybe best answered by Doctor Calusi.

987
01:45:43,810 --> 01:45:47,332
that a resident sent to me and asked that we answer.

988
01:45:47,432 --> 01:45:57,659
So there are some questions around sort of the need and the intended usage of particular spaces.

989
01:45:57,779 --> 01:46:03,303
So for example, one of them is some of the variants we're considering from the auditorium.

990
01:46:04,424 --> 01:46:11,229
So for those of you who are following the auditorium, we have options right now for 750,

991
01:46:13,303 --> 01:46:14,164
500, 800, and 1,000 seats.

992
01:46:14,264 --> 01:46:21,030
So can you talk a little bit about where we started and how these options came to be and the vision for that space?

993
01:46:21,350 --> 01:46:21,931
Absolutely.

994
01:46:21,951 --> 01:46:23,752
Let's move it so people at home can hear.

995
01:46:24,613 --> 01:46:25,734
Oh, wait.

996
01:46:25,754 --> 01:46:26,334
Where to start?

997
01:46:26,454 --> 01:46:33,040
So right now, I think it's important to note currently our auditorium holds, I would say, roughly 330 seats.

998
01:46:33,781 --> 01:46:35,562
However, many of them are broken.

999
01:46:35,802 --> 01:46:38,905
So in reality, it's more closer to probably 300 seats.

1000
01:46:40,845 --> 01:46:44,067
And there are about 1,200 students in this building.

1001
01:46:44,807 --> 01:47:03,297
So not only do we have a very thriving arts program and theater program growing every year, but we also, right now, the principal has very limited space in which to gather grade levels of students.

1002
01:47:03,857 --> 01:47:08,400
So in order to have a school assembly or grade level assemblies,

1003
01:47:09,485 --> 01:47:13,967
Anything instructional, speaker series, it's really just the gymnasium.

1004
01:47:15,027 --> 01:47:28,432
And for some events, that might be appropriate, but if we're talking about speaker series or having any sort of projection opportunities, it gets very cumbersome and challenging.

1005
01:47:29,773 --> 01:47:32,834
Just so you understand, like, part of the need and the want.

1006
01:47:33,516 --> 01:47:38,741
So, 1 of the things we did with the project team is the principal myself, the director of arts.

1007
01:47:39,762 --> 01:47:40,904
We also had a meeting.

1008
01:47:41,624 --> 01:47:46,690
We, with some theater experts, we also have 1 on our building committee.

1009
01:47:47,290 --> 01:47:50,974
Mr Malone joined that meeting and we did have a conversation.

1010
01:47:51,114 --> 01:47:51,835
I learned a lot.

1011
01:47:52,540 --> 01:47:58,822
about theaters in that conversation, because it involved the total space.

1012
01:48:00,143 --> 01:48:10,907
And I will say that I was someone that very much was advocating for the 1,000 seat space, thinking that we have a school that's about 1,200.

1013
01:48:11,967 --> 01:48:19,410
And I would say that came out of that conversation with some of the people talking about performance and intimate spaces.

1014
01:48:20,417 --> 01:48:29,521
and how voice projects, how sound projects, and just the overall experience when you're in that space.

1015
01:48:30,761 --> 01:48:39,265
There was also a lot of suggestion to make the seat spaces smaller so that the performance space is a little bit more.

1016
01:48:40,285 --> 01:48:46,088
Knowing also additionally that the thousand seats aren't going to be able to fit the entire school community.

1017
01:48:46,975 --> 01:48:54,900
And maybe the bowl is fitting half of the school community, so that you have some flexibility, but you're also keeping that space.

1018
01:48:55,441 --> 01:49:03,246
So it was important for us to see what the estimates would be for multiple iterations of spaces.

1019
01:49:03,786 --> 01:49:06,828
MSBA, I believe, covers seven- Up to 750.

1020
01:49:07,409 --> 01:49:12,492
Up to 750, which is why we have a range from 500 to 750 that you have to allow.

1021
01:49:14,830 --> 01:49:16,732
So that's number one.

1022
01:49:16,752 --> 01:49:17,873
Okay.

1023
01:49:18,073 --> 01:49:19,955
Number two is the community meeting space.

1024
01:49:20,135 --> 01:49:22,657
So I will happily take that one.

1025
01:49:23,158 --> 01:49:24,659
So the community meeting space.

1026
01:49:25,360 --> 01:49:31,005
One of the things that was envisioned as we talked about that space was like

1027
01:49:31,328 --> 01:49:35,771
There's like four meetings going on tonight across the city in various capacities.

1028
01:49:36,391 --> 01:49:49,920
And I think there is a real desire for lots of residents who want to be able to come to meetings in person, and they want, when they're in person, to be able to hear and see, which you're all struggling through right now, as we know.

1029
01:49:50,781 --> 01:49:54,543
But they also want, if they want to watch from home, they want to be able to hear and see.

1030
01:49:55,144 --> 01:49:59,987
And we have one space in the entire city that can handle that kind of meeting

1031
01:50:00,638 --> 01:50:06,600
in addition to really two spaces in the entire city that are set up for like gathering.

1032
01:50:06,620 --> 01:50:10,642
So we have the foster care room and the library, and then we have the chamber.

1033
01:50:11,162 --> 01:50:25,787
And so the concept of the community meeting space was to create another space in the city for use by the community for all of the various reasons why meetings happen, whether it's bringing in a speaker for

1034
01:50:26,508 --> 01:50:35,173
AI with your, you know, handling like the advent of AI with your children, with your five-year-olds or having a public meeting or having a public hearing.

1035
01:50:35,673 --> 01:50:51,343
And so what we did was try to say, if we are going to have a space like that, how do we do that in compliance with the rules and requirements and laws around having public meetings and having open space for meetings and enough capacity.

1036
01:50:51,403 --> 01:50:53,404
So that is sort of the genesis of the

1037
01:50:54,358 --> 01:50:57,101
the community meeting were those public meetings.

1038
01:50:57,801 --> 01:51:09,791
At the same time, I had a chance to go to Malden High School where they have a community meeting room of sorts and for an award ceremony.

1039
01:51:09,871 --> 01:51:15,636
And one of the things that was so interesting about that space is we were there for an award ceremony at nine o'clock in the morning.

1040
01:51:17,077 --> 01:51:22,722
Public could get into and out of that space without interrupting school operations whatsoever.

1041
01:51:23,804 --> 01:51:25,106
There was an outside entrance.

1042
01:51:25,146 --> 01:51:26,327
There was a way to get in.

1043
01:51:26,367 --> 01:51:33,132
There was a way to have the meeting completely closed off of the school, but entire school was continuing to operate as it was this space.

1044
01:51:33,273 --> 01:51:33,613
It's like.

1045
01:51:34,083 --> 01:51:41,206
sort of a big rectangular room, like I might not pick a rectangle, but it was a big rectangular room and it clearly gets a lot of use.

1046
01:51:41,346 --> 01:51:53,371
And so when we were talking about what goes in the space summary, this was really a chance for us in a global way to explore all things that are possible, right?

1047
01:51:53,791 --> 01:51:57,093
And so the community meeting room was one of those spaces that

1048
01:51:57,758 --> 01:52:00,218
was requested and envisioned.

1049
01:52:00,459 --> 01:52:04,879
And I have heard from countless residents that we lack that kind of space in Bedford.

1050
01:52:05,159 --> 01:52:09,820
Now, are we going to go build that space somewhere else, like in a standalone fashion?

1051
01:52:10,240 --> 01:52:12,541
Probably not, maybe never.

1052
01:52:13,481 --> 01:52:21,863
And so if we're talking about having an opportunity to do that here inside the confines of this project in some way, it's worth exploring.

1053
01:52:22,303 --> 01:52:24,203
And so that is a thing that we are exploring.

1054
01:52:26,587 --> 01:52:28,368
The next one is the Loans.

1055
01:52:30,548 --> 01:52:35,909
Welcome Center, aka Registration, aka Parent Information Center.

1056
01:52:36,090 --> 01:52:43,311
It has lots of names, but as you know, when you enter the lobby here at Medford High School, that is our registration office.

1057
01:52:43,451 --> 01:52:49,533
We like to refer to it as a Welcome Center, so that's why I like to name how we want families to feel when they come here.

1058
01:52:51,027 --> 01:53:00,092
So much so we've created a little hub around our welcome center so that when families come in, they can have all of their questions answered.

1059
01:53:00,392 --> 01:53:03,274
They have adjacent supports as needed.

1060
01:53:04,335 --> 01:53:08,497
For example, behind this wall is our EL department.

1061
01:53:09,538 --> 01:53:13,200
Many of our students that come to Medford registered here.

1062
01:53:14,133 --> 01:53:16,154
also require some additional supports.

1063
01:53:16,234 --> 01:53:26,399
They may require some language testing so that we can determine the appropriate supports for those students in schools, the appropriate assignments.

1064
01:53:26,859 --> 01:53:30,801
We also have special education located right next to our Welcome Center.

1065
01:53:30,861 --> 01:53:33,602
We have nursing, as you know.

1066
01:53:34,368 --> 01:53:37,029
Medical needs are part of the registration process.

1067
01:53:37,389 --> 01:53:41,790
We have transportation right here, and we have MFN also right here.

1068
01:53:42,110 --> 01:53:58,355
So all around our Welcome Center for families to come here are all of the adjacencies that are needed to support families to get their questions answered, to help with any sort of assessments, assignments, and just wraparound services.

1069
01:54:01,172 --> 01:54:03,374
And the Welcome Center is housed here today.

1070
01:54:03,534 --> 01:54:25,173
So yes, there was, if we go all the way back to the beginning, which was like in 2022, really, when we submitted our first statement of interest for this iteration of our statement of interest that was ultimately successful, we always endeavored to rehome all of the programming that was in this building.

1071
01:54:25,519 --> 01:54:27,141
So that was part of our statement of interest.

1072
01:54:27,622 --> 01:54:32,989
It talked about the Welcome Center, it talked about the MFN, it talked about central office, it talked about all of those spaces.

1073
01:54:33,049 --> 01:54:38,676
So it was always the school committee's intention and plan to continue to house those spaces.

1074
01:54:39,654 --> 01:54:42,957
The plan always has been that they would be here because they've always been.

1075
01:54:43,178 --> 01:54:44,939
Now, is that the right reason to have them here?

1076
01:54:44,959 --> 01:54:45,880
Maybe not.

1077
01:54:47,102 --> 01:54:52,387
And what we are doing now when we start talking about a high school only option is saying, well, what if they work somewhere else?

1078
01:54:52,727 --> 01:54:55,911
Does that improve the quality of programming?

1079
01:54:57,638 --> 01:55:01,039
improve accessibility, does it save costs?

1080
01:55:01,359 --> 01:55:13,823
There's a lot of things to explore there, but over the course of three full school committees now, the school committee has been steadfast in the value of these programs and the things that are happening in this building.

1081
01:55:15,224 --> 01:55:24,227
The pre-K programming was always here for many, many years and was moved out, and there's a great debate for us to have at some point in time about

1082
01:55:25,265 --> 01:55:29,866
whether centralized or decentralized programming is beneficial for pre-K students.

1083
01:55:30,766 --> 01:55:34,167
And we'll have that debate at some point in the near future.

1084
01:55:34,227 --> 01:55:46,790
But the school committee as the like holder of the sort of application process and the council through its affirmation has always said that these programs are important to Medford.

1085
01:55:47,530 --> 01:55:52,371
I think you all probably are seeing and hearing about the Medford Family Networks,

1086
01:55:53,266 --> 01:55:56,888
loss of a grant and the way that that throws that program into question.

1087
01:55:57,408 --> 01:56:00,569
Nobody in Medford wants to see the Medford Family Network go away.

1088
01:56:00,970 --> 01:56:16,517
It provides critical resources, and more importantly, it has huge potential to continue to provide services that are a little bit different than they are today to reach more families here in Medford as Medford's families change over the course of time.

1089
01:56:17,643 --> 01:56:26,306
All of those things have always been part of the plan, simply put, and really the cost is causing us to say, is it the best plan?

1090
01:56:26,826 --> 01:56:37,169
And so stepping back and evaluating, is this the best plan, or is there another better plan, is what will happen as we go forward with some of that.

1091
01:56:37,229 --> 01:56:40,130
Can I just say one small thing, too, about Kids Corner?

1092
01:56:40,190 --> 01:56:41,450
It's our municipal daycare.

1093
01:56:42,031 --> 01:56:43,091
It serves our teachers.

1094
01:56:43,171 --> 01:56:46,112
It serves anyone that works within the city of Medford.

1095
01:56:47,660 --> 01:56:55,444
It does also serve some community families for space when there's open enrollment, and it also serves our students.

1096
01:56:56,305 --> 01:57:06,169
So if we have students that require daycare so that they can finish their high school education and graduate, we also provide that here for our students.

1097
01:57:06,670 --> 01:57:13,273
And I would say one of the things, it's a very tight space right now, and there are wait lists.

1098
01:57:13,726 --> 01:57:26,237
And so from community members, especially, so this would also offer an opportunity to enlarge that opportunity, daycare opportunity within the city for a lot of our families.

1099
01:57:28,039 --> 01:57:32,863
The next item was teen health center.

1100
01:57:33,224 --> 01:57:37,588
No, I can try and then you can add on.

1101
01:57:37,748 --> 01:57:38,889
I will admit that I'm not.

1102
01:57:39,719 --> 01:57:56,886
as well versed about the teen health center as any of the other spaces in the school, but the teen health center would be, would serve between both the office of our nursing and as well as the office of our behavioral health and school counseling programs.

1103
01:57:57,386 --> 01:58:08,491
So that this would provide just satellite space for medical or social workers, health, mental health workers,

1104
01:58:08,972 --> 01:58:19,477
to have the space here to be working and supporting and serving some of our students based on whatever their needs are.

1105
01:58:19,937 --> 01:58:35,844
This would need to be adjacent to the nursing program for confidentiality and to kind of acquire space, but it would be that there is a separate dedicated office and room used for outside consultants.

1106
01:58:35,964 --> 01:58:37,685
We do currently have that,

1107
01:58:38,162 --> 01:58:42,924
with Cambridge Health and some other consultants.

1108
01:58:43,324 --> 01:58:48,106
We do have Dr. Safia, who is our district pediatrician.

1109
01:58:48,666 --> 01:59:07,334
And so we may do what we can, but this space also comes here and sometimes provides some medical care for our students, especially around sports and athletics in providing physicals for students that may not have that immediate access within the college.

1110
01:59:08,608 --> 01:59:33,382
And then I will say part of the conversation in the very beginning of the team health center with Dr. Xavier and Director Silva was that to create capacity, to have a space more like a Cambridge Health Alliance to co-locate here would improve access to health care for students who are lacking that access, right?

1111
01:59:33,722 --> 01:59:37,824
And those programs, they are all very quite different, but Cambridge Health Alliance

1112
01:59:38,375 --> 01:59:44,278
would operate sort of independently of our school, but also within our school.

1113
01:59:44,338 --> 01:59:49,480
And there's a lot of grant funding that comes with those programs to open teen health centers in high schools.

1114
01:59:50,541 --> 01:59:57,404
So that was the genesis, again, to explore, which was to say, we can never do that if there is no space for it.

1115
01:59:57,444 --> 02:00:06,708
But if there is a space for it, could we create a collaborative partnership with a reputable provider in the community and provide access to care

1116
02:00:07,212 --> 02:00:09,873
for our students here in this building.

1117
02:00:09,973 --> 02:00:21,217
So beyond what Dr. Sabia is able to do sort of in his life, in the limited time he has to come here, like really to have standing health care, like Malden High does have a teen health center under several

1118
02:00:22,072 --> 02:00:23,713
big schools that do provide that.

1119
02:00:23,773 --> 02:00:29,776
So that was the genesis of saying, we should look at this and decide if that is something you want to go forward with.

1120
02:00:29,896 --> 02:00:32,258
But another thing is there has to be space.

1121
02:00:32,298 --> 02:00:32,998
Yes, yes.

1122
02:00:33,258 --> 02:00:35,980
And full transparency, the grant requires that.

1123
02:00:36,220 --> 02:00:42,483
So the grant funding that Jenny mentioned requires separate space, not a shared space.

1124
02:00:44,184 --> 02:00:47,886
And then the last piece is additional fields.

1125
02:00:52,414 --> 02:00:53,495
Is this for the fields above?

1126
02:00:54,075 --> 02:00:54,375
Yes.

1127
02:00:56,536 --> 02:01:04,539
I'm just going to be honest, not like slaying anyone, but I am one of those people that would love to see if ever we could do it.

1128
02:01:06,240 --> 02:01:07,781
The track and football fields here.

1129
02:01:08,401 --> 02:01:11,142
I say that for a couple of reasons, purely around equity.

1130
02:01:11,582 --> 02:01:16,264
I know that the high school, Medford High School, is not situated in the center of Medford.

1131
02:01:16,804 --> 02:01:17,965
So we

1132
02:01:18,525 --> 02:01:24,288
The location of Benford High School can be challenging for some of our families, and I have to just acknowledge that.

1133
02:01:24,808 --> 02:01:28,510
However, this is the space and the land that we have to use for this project.

1134
02:01:28,931 --> 02:01:33,873
And so right now, currently, we have sports programs and we have our band.

1135
02:01:34,614 --> 02:01:38,296
Our band practices in the parking lot right out front.

1136
02:01:39,076 --> 02:01:45,099
And if they're lucky enough, they can get to go practice at Hormel, which is really where they're performing.

1137
02:01:47,238 --> 02:01:52,084
I so I personally would love to see that here if if ever at all possible.

1138
02:01:52,224 --> 02:01:57,510
And because of that, I wouldn't want to see a space like fields be eliminated.

1139
02:01:58,051 --> 02:02:04,558
So I would I would love to be able to prioritize as much field space as possible.

1140
02:02:04,999 --> 02:02:07,141
And I think the way to probably do that.

1141
02:02:07,242 --> 02:02:07,502
I know

1142
02:02:08,245 --> 02:02:14,769
can't always have everything, but a way to do that is to have the field on top of the parking garage.

1143
02:02:15,209 --> 02:02:33,880
Part of this process, lots of teams of people on the school building committee, our staff, our teachers, our administrators, we've done lots of school tours, and we were able to see this in action at Waltham High School, which was recently done, 2023,

1144
02:02:39,522 --> 02:02:43,484
They have fields on top of a parking garage and it's their soccer field.

1145
02:02:44,264 --> 02:02:46,345
And it was fascinating to be able to see.

1146
02:02:46,365 --> 02:02:58,470
I would tell you I have mixed feelings about a parking garage, but maintaining as much space as we can for our students and community use is definitely a priority.

1147
02:02:59,610 --> 02:03:01,551
Yeah, I'll just tack on to that.

1148
02:03:02,952 --> 02:03:03,972
We are at like a

1149
02:03:04,483 --> 02:03:06,744
premium for field space in Medford, right?

1150
02:03:06,784 --> 02:03:11,325
Again, we don't have endless amounts of space that we can sort of open up and make a new field.

1151
02:03:12,285 --> 02:03:15,206
So if you have kids involved in athletics, you know that, right?

1152
02:03:15,846 --> 02:03:20,948
Kids are sort of all over, particularly the high school kids, they're sort of all over the place trying to get to their fields.

1153
02:03:21,368 --> 02:03:28,550
There are kids who leave here, they're football here and have to get to Harmel, which is why they practice on this sort of makeshift field here.

1154
02:03:29,050 --> 02:03:32,372
And then you have kids that run track, they have to get across town.

1155
02:03:32,452 --> 02:03:33,812
So there is an equity issue

1156
02:03:34,382 --> 02:03:40,846
On top of that, there's just a lack of space, right, in Medford for all these kinds of things, and there's huge demand.

1157
02:03:40,926 --> 02:03:44,788
And I think I've seen the demand for, like, Lucas plays soccer.

1158
02:03:45,708 --> 02:03:50,891
The fields are always just, like, sort of wall-to-wall, busy during soccer season.

1159
02:03:51,532 --> 02:03:54,013
The softball field, the baseball field, they're all like that, right?

1160
02:03:54,453 --> 02:04:02,338
So the other sort of value of thinking about bringing the stadium here, the football stadium and track here,

1161
02:04:02,937 --> 02:04:06,778
is if you could co-locate that, that creates a campus feel, right?

1162
02:04:06,898 --> 02:04:18,701
For football games, et cetera, you're at your school, you're on a field, you're at your school, you're behaving like you're at your school, you're not in a place where you're like, this is not my school and I can behave how I want, right?

1163
02:04:19,061 --> 02:04:24,622
So all of those things, bringing them here sort of creates that here.

1164
02:04:25,122 --> 02:04:28,703
The other thing that could do for Medford is,

1165
02:04:29,363 --> 02:04:33,345
allow us to activate Hormel differently than it is today.

1166
02:04:33,865 --> 02:04:39,648
Hormel is situated near vertical grocery stores, public transit, and multiple schools.

1167
02:04:40,088 --> 02:04:54,135
There is an opportunity there for the city to explore, if they choose, to say, what could Hormel be if we co-locate our main stadium here?

1168
02:04:54,175 --> 02:04:57,457
So there's a bigger planning and development vision there.

1169
02:04:59,007 --> 02:05:03,569
I've been talking about that with folks on the council and the mayor for like well over a year now.

1170
02:05:03,629 --> 02:05:08,031
Like first came up when the horse farm, like that sits like up adjacent here, one for sale.

1171
02:05:08,071 --> 02:05:10,092
And I was like, we should buy that for this project.

1172
02:05:10,132 --> 02:05:13,414
And it got scooped up and now it's going to become, you know, 12 houses.

1173
02:05:14,815 --> 02:05:28,241
But like those kinds of opportunities to acquire space and to do the kinds of things that we're trying to do in Wentworth across the board and to activate spaces differently is like a tangential opportunity.

1174
02:05:28,728 --> 02:05:31,590
that's only made possible if we can let people take that.

1175
02:05:31,830 --> 02:05:37,675
Formal also needs a tremendous amount of work on its own for its own project.

1176
02:05:38,095 --> 02:05:46,001
And so the question then becomes like, is there an opportunity to really sort of zoom out and think about what's possible?

1177
02:05:46,101 --> 02:05:50,504
So that's where field over parking sort of came from along with the planning.

1178
02:05:50,884 --> 02:05:54,687
There's an equity piece, there's an activation of Cornell case,

